32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, clarifies that a court
3344 must make findings explaining why the risk of harm to a child is outweighed by the trauma
3355 of the child's removal from the child's home and that the department has exhausted the
3366 options to mitigate the immediate risk of serious harm and avoid the removal of the child
3377 from the child's home after a summary preliminary hearing only if the court finds in favor
3388 of the Department of Health and Human Services and upholds the removal. It also clarifies
3399 that, when the department files a petition to terminate parental rights, it must provide a
4400 detailed statement of the specific reasonable efforts the department has made to reunify the
Page 2 - 132LR0671(02)
